headlines.description: — Kevin Love had 21 points, 10 assists and eight rebounds as the short-handed Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Detroit Pistons 112-88 on Friday night for their seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Love, Allen lead short-handed Cavaliers to rout of Pistons

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 25 points, Bennedict Mathurin had 23 points and Tyrese Haliburton scored 22 to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 101-99 victory over the Miami Heat on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana Pacers hold on to beat Miami Heat 101-99

headlines.description: — Obi Toppin hit a 3-pointer and Jalen Brunson finished off a three-point play seconds later as the New York Knicks rallied from 12 points down to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 106-104 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson, Barrett help Knicks rally to beat 76ers 106-104

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 28 points, 11 assists and nine rebounds, and the Brooklyn Nets won easily in their first game following Kyrie Irving's suspension, 128-86 over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Without suspended Irving, Nets rout Wizards 128-86

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 36 points and 12 rebounds, including some late free throws to help the Boston Celtics hold on for a 123-119 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 36, Celtics rally to hold off Bulls 123-119

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 23 points, matching his career-high with six 3-pointers, and the Memphis Grizzlies ran past the Charlotte Hornets 130-99 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks scores 23 as Grizzlies rout Hornets 130-99

events.name: LA Clippers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 33 points and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied to beat the San Antonio Spurs 113-106 on Friday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Clippers rally past Spurs for 3rd straight victory

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 35 points, his eighth consecutive game of at least 30 to begin the season, as the Dallas Mavericks beat the Toronto Raptors 111-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's 30-point streak hits 8 games as Mavs beat Raptors

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Golden State coach Steve Kerr foreshadowed a plan to adjust playing time across his roster in the coming week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors 0-6 on road, fall to Pelicans with 4 starters out

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 26 points, 13 rebounds and 11 assists, Jrue Holiday scored 29 points and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 115-102 on Friday night to improve to 8-0, the best start to a season in franchise history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis has triple-double, Bucks beat Wolves for 8-0 start

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — The Portland Trail Blazers had 1 second left and a game-winning shot opportunity. The problem was their two biggest game-winning-shot-makers were out with injuries.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant hits jumper at buzzer, Trail Blazers top Suns 108-106

events.name: Utah Jazz at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 27 points and 12 rebounds, Jordan Clarkson added 20 points, and the Utah Jazz continued their remarkable start to the season with a 130-116 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen leads surprising Jazz past Lakers, 130-116
